kylin-screensaver
kylin-screensaver is a fork of mate-screensaver.
=================

kylin-screensaver is a screen saver and locker that aims to have
simple, sane, secure defaults and be well integrated with the desktop.
It is designed to support:

        * the ability to lock down configuration settings
        * translation into many languages
        * user switching


Known Issues
============


Installation
============

See the file 'INSTALL'

./autogen.sh --prefix=/usr --sysconfdir=/etc
make
sudo make install


How to report bugs
==================

Bugs should be reported to the UKUI bug tracking
system:
    https://github.com/ukui/kylin-screensaver/issues

You will need to create an account if you don't have one already.

In the bug report please include information about your system, if possible:

   - What operating system and version

   - What version of kylin-screenaver

        The output of the "kylin-screensaver-command --version" command.

 
